Web hosting —>

1. We can select regions based on our preference, website will load faster to users accessing from that particular region. 
2. Web hosting services provide us with another PC which hosts our website 24/7. 
3. We can access the alotted PC(terminal) with the given Username and Password. 
4.  Enter these in your own PC’s terminal to access the aloted PC —>  ssh username @alottedipaddress then enter password.
5. We use FileZilla server for efficient file managements between both the PCs.
6. make port:22 for file transfer in Filezilla GUI.
7. “npm i dotenv” command is used to install env and make .env file which stores all of the crucial info like password etc. which will be hidden from public.
8. To implement .env and create environment variables for our web app. We include “require ('dotenv'). config() and in next line console.log(process.env)” into our express server file(server.js).
9. To host an Index.html into the hosting PC, install apache web server using “apt install apache2” into the hosting terminal. 
10. This will give us “folder/var/www/html”, we simply have to move our index.html file into this folder using FileZilla for it to be hosted. 
11. Domain name is used to replace IP address, domain name has a variable which points to our IP address hence making it easier for users to search our website.
12. Another alternative to Apache is NGINX.

-Types of hosting —>
1. Shared hosting - Multiple users access a single big powerful computer with their respective username and passwd.
2. Dedicated Hosting - Each user is aloted their own unique PC.
3. Managed Hosting - along with hosting, IT support which inculdes server maintainence and alerts are also provided.
